title: Department of Transport and Main Roads 2023 Queensland Transport and Roads Investment Program (QTRIP) Industry Briefing
agency: Issued by Department of Transport and Main Roads - Program Management & Delivery
description: The Department of Transport and Main Roads (TMR), invites you to an industry briefing on the program of works announced under the Queensland Transport and Roads Investment Program (QTRIP) 2023–24 to 2026–27. The department is hosting an online livestreamed event on Thursday, 31 August 2023 from 1:00pm to 4:15pm. The 2023 QTRIP Industry Briefing will outline current and future departmental initiatives, provide an update on the Transport System Planning Program and the Collaborative Transport Infrastructure Program, as well as presentations from Maritime Safety Queensland, Translink and TMR's Regional Directors.  Following the event, presentations and the recorded briefing session will be uploaded onto TMR's QTRIP website and will be available for viewing from Monday, 4 September 2023 until Friday, 29 September 2023. If you would like to view the 2023 QTRIP Industry Briefing, please register for the livestreamed event via Eventbrite. Registrations will close at 5pm on 29 August 2023. For further information on registering for the 2023 QTRIP Industry Briefing, please email QTRIP_IndustryBriefing@tmr.qld.gov.au. Livestream details The livestream will commence at 1.00pm and can be accessed via the Eventbrite registration confirmation email. Privacy statement Eventbrite’s server is based in the USA. If you register through this site, you agree to your personal information being transferred overseas. Please refer to the Eventbrite privacy policy for more details.

title: Provision of Internal Medical Advisory Services
agency: Issued by Office of Industrial Relations
description: Suppliers are invited by the Customer to submit an offer for ITO No. OIR 131_2223 for the provision of Internal Medical Advisory Services as specified in Part B: Contract Details document.  The Customer is looking to engage with a single Supplier, with a dedicated medical advisor to deliver the required Services. The Office of Industrial Relations (OIR) require an experienced Internal Medical Advisor (Occupational Physician) to provide internal expert medical advisory services across the organisation.
